<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>8-103.13</num>
  <heading>Mayor authorized to regulate construction.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>The Mayor may regulate construction that bears upon the quality of the waters of the District.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>No person shall construct a treatment facility which has not been approved by the Mayor before construction begins.</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 5-188" type="History">Mar. 16, 1985, D.C. Law 5-188, § 14, 32 DCR 919</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 6-933.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>